red herring  n. 1. A smoked herring having a reddish color.
2. Something that draws attention from the matter or issue at
hand. [From its use to distract hunting dogs from the trail.]

     Whether or not you are familiar with the concept of a red
herring, it is something which you will see quite a lot of in
quests, at least the well-coded ones.  A red herring is
something a builder throws into a quest just for giggles and which
has absolutely no purpose in the end.  In other words, if you
know something is a red herring, don't bother doing it as it won't
get you anywhere in terms of completing the quest.  Unfortunately,
you will only know if something was merely a distraction _after_
you complete the quest.
     So what's a player to do?  First, as stated before, try
everything.  If you don't try, you won't know, and then you won't
get anywhere.  Second, don't get caught up on one thing.  If you
can't figure something out, go look around and fiddle with other
things in the area.  It may be that you need another item to do
whatever you're trying to do, or it may be that the problem in
question is just a red herring thrown in to annoy and distract
you.  So be patient, take it easy, and look out for fish.
